###Converting the Expression 

>$\begin{align}\pm\sqrt{-35}&=\pm\sqrt{-1\cdot35}
\\\\&=\pm\sqrt{-1}\cdot\sqrt{35}
\\\\&=\pm\maroonD{i}\cdot\sqrt{35}
\\\\&=\pm\sqrt{35}\maroonD{i}\end{align}$

###Finding $a$ 

For $\goldE{|z_1|}=\goldE{2}$ and $\blueD{\theta_1}=\blueD{49^{\circ}}$, we can find $\maroonD{a}$ as follows.


$\begin{align}\maroonD{a}&=\goldE{|z_1|}\cos\blueD{\theta_1}
\\\\&=\goldE{2}\cos\blueD{49^\circ}
\\\\&=\maroonD{1.312}\end{align}$

###Finding $b$ 

$\begin{align}\tealD{b}&=\goldE{|z_1|}\sin\blueD{\theta_1}
\\\\&=\goldE{2}\sin\blueD{49^\circ}
\\\\&=\tealD{1.509}\end{align}$

###Take the absolute value of the difference 

$\begin{align}|z_1-z_2|&=|(-5)+(0)i|
\\\\&=\sqrt{(-5)^2+(0)^2}
\\\\&=\sqrt{25+0}
\\\\&=\sqrt{25}
\\\\&=5\end{align}$

###Find the midpoint of $z_1$ and $z_2$ 

The midpoint $m$ occurs at the average of $z_1$ and $z_2$: 

>$\begin{align}m&=\dfrac{z_1+z_2}{2}
\\\\&=\dfrac{(9+7i)+(-7+7i)}{2}
\\\\&=\dfrac{9-7+7i+7i}{2}
\\\\&=\dfrac{2+14i}{2}
\\\\&=1+7i\end{align}$

